$ PowerShell: comma operator

The comma operator can be used to create → Windows/PowerShell/language/type/array[arrays]:
code {
$ary = $elem_one, $elem_two, $elem_three
code }

There is also a unary comma operator which creates an array with one element only. Note that the comman needs to be placed *before* the element:
code {
$ary = ,42
code }

sa:
  → Windows/PowerShell/language/operator[operators]
